common.name: Bluethroat
notes: I returned to the spot where Iâ€™d seen the agitated female Bluethroat earlier in the day. Iâ€™d found a Bluethroat nest 20 years ago on the Yukonâ€™s North Slope â€” so knew the kind of nesting micro-habitat yo search. I walked slowly along the edge of a small berm running at the base of a hillside along the alluvial fan. As I neared the spot where Iâ€™d seen the female, I focused intently on suitable-looking nest sites. And then she flushed, just a few metres ahead. The nest was then easy enough to see; a grass-cup ground nest at the base of low willows along the south-east facing hillside. Four bluish-green eggs with a brownish cast at the end. I took a few quick record photos, and moved along. This is only the second-ever nest record for Canada, and a first for Qikiqtaruk.
